Install
=======

This project currently supports two practical build paths:

1. UBOONE/GPVM-style environment with CVMFS
2. Docker-based build environment

GPVM Build
----------

This is the native path the repository was originally written around.

Prerequisites:

- CVMFS mounted and accessible
- UBOONE/Fermilab environment commands available
- ROOT available through that environment

From the repository root:

```bash
source ./.setup.sh
make
```

Build outputs:

- `build/lib/libIO.so`
- `build/bin/mk_sample`

Notes:

- `mk_sample` can use the site-local beam database default if it exists:
  `/exp/uboone/data/uboonebeam/beamdb/run.db`
- You can override that path at runtime with:

```bash
build/bin/mk_sample --run-db /path/to/run.db output.root input.list data nominal numi fhc
```

Docker Build
------------

This is the cleanest portable path outside GPVM/CVMFS.

Build the image from the repository root:

```bash
docker build -t amarantin-dev .
```

Run a shell in the container with the repo mounted at `/work`:

```bash
docker run --rm -it \
  -v "$PWD":/work \
  -w /work \
  amarantin-dev
```

Then build inside the container:

```bash
make
```

Direct one-shot build without opening a shell:

```bash
docker run --rm \
  -v "$PWD":/work \
  -w /work \
  amarantin-dev \
  make
```

Build outputs:

- `build/lib/libIO.so`
- `build/bin/mk_sample`

Optional mounts for data and beam DB:

```bash
docker run --rm -it \
  -v "$PWD":/work \
  -v /path/to/data:/data:ro \
  -v /path/to/run.db:/opt/run.db:ro \
  -w /work \
  amarantin-dev
```

Example runtime command inside the container:

```bash
build/bin/mk_sample --run-db /opt/run.db output.root input.list data nominal numi fhc
```

Platform note:

- The current Docker image was built from an `amd64` ROOT base image.
- On Apple Silicon or other `arm64` hosts, Docker may run it under emulation.
- The build has been verified successfully under that emulated path.
